JDK (java development kit) --> is a software development environment used for developing and 
running Java applications and applets. it comprises java runtime environment which is just used 
to run java programs.JDK is platform dependant
		 
		                              WHILE
		                              
JVM (Java virtual Machine)--> is a virtual machine that enables a 
computer to run Java programs as well as programs written in other languages, it converts 
java byte code into machine language. JVM is not platform independant
		
		
		
	}